    }, 
    {
        "text": "Minority Ethic Groups in Sapa", 
        "line": 34, 
        "range": [
            3976, 
            4004
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4001, 
                    4005
                ], 
                "name": "Sapa"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 35, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "There are mainly 5 ethnic groups in Sapa: Hmong, Dao, Tay, Giay, and a small number of Xa Pho. Majority are Hmong. Hmong Tribe was originally came from yellow river region in China.", 
        "line": 36, 
        "range": [
            4006, 
            4186
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4043, 
                    4047
                ], 
                "name": "Sapa"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    4159, 
                    4178
                ], 
                "name": "yellow river region"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4182, 
                    4187
                ], 
                "name": "China"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 37, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "There was a massive migration by Hmong People in 18th century due to armed conflict. The Hmong spread across mountainous regions in China, Vietnam, Laos, and Thailand. The Hmong in Sapa itself is divided in several subgroups such as Black Hmong and Red Hmong.", 
        "line": 38, 
        "range": [
            4188, 
            4446
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NOM", 
                "span": [
                    4299, 
                    4318
                ], 
                "name": "mountainous regions"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4322, 
                    4327
                ], 
                "name": "China"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4329, 
                    4336
                ], 
                "name": "Vietnam"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4338, 
                    4342
                ], 
                "name": "Laos"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4348, 
                    4356
                ], 
                "name": "Thailand"
            }, 
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4371, 
                    4375
                ], 
                "name": "Sapa"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 39, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "The people of Sapa rely on agriculture. They have been very poor even by Vietnam\u2019s rural standard. Thanks to some NGOs who improve social development by giving opportunities such as volunteer program, and programs to increase awareness from tourism sector.", 
        "line": 40, 
        "range": [
            4448, 
            4705
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
                "type": "LOC_NAME", 
                "span": [
                    4465, 
                    4469
                ], 
                "name": "Sapa"
            }
        ]
    }, 
    {
        "text": "", 
        "line": 41, 
        "range": [], 
        "entities": []
    }, 
    {
        "text": "To be honest, I regret myself taking a tour due to limited time. I would rather rent a motorbike and ride to the villages cause when I did the trekking tour, mostly I walked on the main road which was accessible by motorbike. But, it was good experience for me, spending a night in local house, and cooked by local Hmong. I\u2019ll surely want to go back to Sapa.", 
        "line": 42, 
        "range": [
            4707, 
            5066
        ], 
        "entities": [
            {
